The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 21 January is 177,197 (20,423 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 16 January, there were 7,462 new confirmed cases (860.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 09 January, there were 10,506 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 29% (3,044 fewer cases).
